                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/17.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-04-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 26, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>201. Department has received from American Consul, Nogales, notice that
                    insurrectionary forces are collecting taxes on mines and other property.
                    Department is advising Consulate as follows: [Quotes telegram to Consul
                    Simpich.]</p>
                <p>You will bring this matter immediately to the attention of the appropriate
                    authorities in the sense indicated in the instruction to the Consul.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
